# Sparkit Privacy Policy

Last Updated: May 23 2026

Welcome to Sparkit. Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how Sparkit collects, uses, stores, and protects your information when you use the Sparkit app and related services.

By using Sparkit, you agree to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.

---

# 1. Information We Collect

When you use Sparkit, we may collect certain information to provide and improve our services.

This may include:

* Account information such as your name, email address, and profile details
* Images, screenshots, and homework questions uploaded through the app
* Usage data such as app activity, feature usage, and interaction history
* Device information, including device type, operating system version, app performance data, IP address, and identifiers that may help us detect abuse, spam, fraud, unauthorized access, or misuse of the platform
* Subscription and purchase information processed through Apple or authorized payment providers

---

# 2. How We Use Information

We use the collected information to:

* Provide homework help and educational features
* Improve Sparkit’s AI systems and overall user experience
* Personalize responses and app functionality
* Maintain account functionality and sync user progress
* Monitor app performance, reliability, and security
* Prevent abuse, spam, fraud, unauthorized access, or misuse of the platform, including through moderation and security systems
* Develop future educational features and tools

Anonymized and aggregated usage data may be used to improve Sparkit’s AI systems and service quality.

---

# 3. AI-Generated Responses

Sparkit uses artificial intelligence to generate educational responses and explanations.

While we work to provide accurate and helpful information, AI-generated content may occasionally contain errors or inaccuracies. Users should always verify important answers independently.

Sparkit is designed to support learning and studying, not replace critical thinking or classroom instruction.

---

# 4. Academic Integrity

Sparkit is intended for educational support and responsible studying.

We do not encourage cheating, academic dishonesty, or misuse of educational tools during tests, exams, or restricted assignments.

In the future, Sparkit may introduce systems designed to encourage responsible educational use and help detect potential misuse of the platform.

Users are responsible for following their school’s academic integrity policies.

---

# 5. Data Storage and Retention

We take reasonable measures to protect user data and maintain the security of our systems.

Certain information may be retained for operational, security, analytics, legal, or service improvement purposes, even after content or accounts are deleted.

We work to protect stored information using industry-standard security practices where reasonably possible.

---

# 6. Sharing of Information

Sparkit does not sell your personal information to third parties.

We may work with trusted third-party services that help operate Sparkit, including:

* Cloud hosting providers
* Analytics platforms
* Authentication services
* AI and processing providers
* Payment and subscription platforms

These services are only given access to the information necessary to perform their functions.

---

# 7. Third-Party Services

Sparkit may use third-party services such as:

* Apple Sign In
* AI processing providers
* Analytics services
* Subscription management platforms

These services may collect and process information according to their own privacy policies.

---

# 8. Children’s Privacy

Sparkit is designed for students and educational use.

We do not knowingly collect personal information from children in violation of applicable laws. If you believe a child has provided personal information improperly, please contact us so we can investigate and take appropriate action.

---

# 9. Your Choices

You may:

* Update account information
* Delete uploaded content within the app
* Request account deletion
* Stop using Sparkit at any time

Some information may still be retained for operational, security, legal, or service-related purposes.

---

# 10. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time as Sparkit evolves.

When significant changes are made, we may notify users through the app or other appropriate methods.

Continued use of Sparkit after updates means you agree to the revised policy.

